                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d726">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11/1694: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-28T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 28, 1933—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 28—5:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>286. British Legation has now received instructions and drafted note to Foreign
                    Office refusing to assent to a further postponement of the Boxer Indemnity
                    payments. Italian Legation still without instructions. I am drafting note of
                    refusal to be submitted by telegraph for Peck<note n="47" xml:id="d726fn47"
                        >Willys R. Peck, Consul General at Nanking; also Counselor of Legation in
                        China.</note> to deliver to the Foreign Office immediately upon receipt of
                    knowledge that Italian Legation has instructions to make similar reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
